# Site date & time formats

BattleDrop reads display defaults from `public.site_settings` (singleton row). Admins edit them at `/admin-panel/settings`. Signed-in users can override date/time display at `/settings` (not site name or slogan).

## Priority

For each of `dateFormat`, `timeFormat`, and `dateSeparator`:

1. **User preference** — `public.users.date_format`, `time_format`, `date_separator` (nullable)
2. **Site default** — `public.site_settings` when the user value is `null`
3. **Hardcoded fallback** — `DEFAULT_SITE_SETTINGS` in `app/lib/site-settings-types.ts`

Merge with `resolveEffectiveDateTimeSettings()` in `app/lib/site-settings/resolve-effective-date-time-settings.ts`.

For the signed-in viewer, prefer `getEffectiveDateTimeSettingsForUser(userId)` in `app/lib/users/user-date-time-preferences.ts`. Guests use site settings only.

## Source of truth

| Layer | What |
|-------|------|
| DB site | `site_name`, `site_slogan`, `date_format`, `time_format`, `date_separator` |
| DB user | `date_format`, `time_format`, `date_separator` (all nullable) |
| Server read site | `getSiteSettings()` in `app/lib/site-settings/get-site-settings.ts` |
| Server read user | `getUserDateTimePreferences()` / fields on `getCurrentAppUser()` |
| Types & low-level formatters | `app/lib/site-settings-types.ts` |
| App helpers | `app/lib/site-settings/format-display-date.ts` |
| User API | `PATCH /api/user-settings` (auth required; date/time only) |
| Admin API | `PATCH /api/site-settings` (admin only) |

## Never use locale formatters for user-visible dates

```typescript
// BAD — bypasses site/user settings
new Date(value).toLocaleString()
new Date(value).toLocaleDateString()
```

## Always use site formatters

```typescript
// Server components / route handlers
import { getEffectiveDateTimeSettingsForUser } from "@/app/lib/users/user-date-time-preferences";
import {
  formatDisplayDate,
  formatDisplayDateTime,
  formatLastSeen,
} from "@/app/lib/site-settings/format-display-date";

const settings = await getEffectiveDateTimeSettingsForUser(userId);
formatDisplayDateTime(user.last_seen, settings);
formatDisplayDate(project.created_at, settings);
```

```typescript
// Client components — read from context (root layout merges user + site)
import { useSiteDateSettings } from "@/app/components/site-date-settings-provider";
import { formatBattleWeekRange } from "@/app/lib/battle-week";

const dateSettings = useSiteDateSettings();
formatBattleWeekRange(week, year, dateSettings);
```

Root layout passes **effective** settings (user overrides applied) into `SiteDateSettingsProvider`.

## Function guide

| Function | Use when |
|----------|----------|
| `resolveEffectiveDateTimeSettings(site, userPrefs?)` | Merge user + site date/time fields |
| `getEffectiveDateTimeSettingsForUser(userId)` | Server: resolved settings for one viewer |
| `formatDisplayDateTime(iso, settings?)` | Date + time (timestamps) |
| `formatDisplayDate(iso, settings?)` | Date only (saved / updated) |
| `formatLastSeen(iso, settings?)` | Relative (< 1 min → seconds, < 1 h → minutes, < 1 d → hours, < 1 w → days; else date) |
| `formatSiteDate(date, settings)` | `Date` object, date part only |
| `formatSiteDateTime(date, settings)` | `Date` object, date + time |
| `formatBattleWeekRange(week, year, settings)` | ISO week range on home hero |

Optional `settings` falls back to `DEFAULT_SITE_SETTINGS`.

## After changing formats

- Admin: `PATCH /api/site-settings` calls `revalidateTag("site-settings")`.
- User: `PATCH /api/user-settings` then `router.refresh()` on the settings form so layout reloads provider values.

## Settings pages

| Route | Who | Editable |
|-------|-----|----------|
| `/admin-panel/settings` | Admin | Site name, slogan, date/time defaults |
| `/settings` | Signed-in user | Date/time only; account info in side panel |

## Exceptions

- Copyright year in footer: `new Date().getFullYear()` is fine
- Archive month section headers (`JUNE`): month name labels, not full dates
- Internal storage / APIs: keep ISO-8601 (`toISOString()`)

When showing a timestamp **for a specific user** (e.g. last seen in admin), resolve that user's effective settings — not the viewer's and not site-only.
